            "id": "start",
            "summary": "Kids discover a magical paintbrush in a museum that transports them",
            "text": "The museum is quiet after closing time. {{PLAYER1_NAME}} and {{PLAYER2_NAME}} are helping their aunt, a museum curator, organize a new exhibit on Renaissance art.\n\n'Be careful with that!' Aunt Sofia calls as {{PLAYER1_NAME}} picks up an old paintbrush from a dusty crate. The brush looks ancient‚Äîits wooden handle worn smooth, its bristles somehow still perfect.\n\nThe moment {{PLAYER2_NAME}} touches it too, the brush begins to glow. Colors swirl around them like a living painting‚Äîdeep blues, vibrant reds, shimmering golds.\n\nWhen the colors fade, they're standing in a cobblestone street. The air smells of paint and woodsmoke. People in strange old-fashioned clothes hurry past.\n\n'Welcome to Florence,' says a voice. A young man with paint-stained hands grins at them. 'The year is 1504. I am Giuliano, apprentice to the great masters. That brush you hold‚Äîit belongs to the workshop of Leonardo da Vinci himself! Come, he will want to meet you.'",
