        "brush-history": {
            "id": "brush-history",
            "summary": "Giuliano explains the brush absorbs genius and transports worthy seekers",
            "text": "'This brush,' Giuliano says reverently, 'is no ordinary tool. It has been passed through the hands of the greatest artists in history. They say it absorbs a bit of their genius, their vision, their passion for beauty.'\n\nHe gently touches the bristles. 'And sometimes, it chooses people‚Äîbrings them here to learn. You must have something special in you. A spark waiting to be kindled.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} looks at the brush with new wonder. 'So it's magical?'\n\n'Magic? Perhaps. Or perhaps art itself is the magic‚Äîthe ability to create something from nothing, to share what you see and feel with others across centuries. The brush simply... opens doors.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} grips it tighter. 'Will it take us home?'\n\n'When your apprenticeship is complete,' Giuliano smiles mysteriously. 'Now come! The masters are waiting. Would you learn from Leonardo the inventor? Michelangelo the sculptor? Or perhaps Botticelli the painter of dreams?'",
