        "leonardo-workshop": {
            "id": "leonardo-workshop",
            "summary": "They meet Leonardo da Vinci surrounded by inventions and studies",
            "text": "The workshop is chaos‚Äîbeautiful chaos. Sketches cover every wall. A half-built flying machine hangs from the ceiling. Jars hold mysterious specimens. Mirrors, gears, and unfinished paintings compete for space.\n\nIn the center, a man with a long beard writes backward in a notebook while simultaneously sketching a human arm.\n\n'Maestro Leonardo,' Giuliano announces. 'Young visitors who seek to learn.'\n\nLeonardo looks up with curious, intense eyes. 'Ah! Fresh minds! Tell me‚Äîwhat do you see when you look at your hand?'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} looks at {{PLAYER2_HIS_HER}} hand. 'Um... fingers?'\n\n'Fingers, yes, but look deeper!' Leonardo leaps up and shows them his sketches. 'Bones, muscles, tendons, blood vessels! To draw a hand, you must understand how it works. Art is not just seeing‚Äîit is knowing. I dissect bodies to understand anatomy. I study birds to understand flight. I observe water to understand flow.'\n\nHe taps his forehead. 'An artist must be a scientist too. Curiosity is the mother of all art.'",
