        "michelangelo-studio": {
            "id": "michelangelo-studio",
            "summary": "They find Michelangelo covered in marble dust, working on David",
            "text": "The sound of chiseling echoes through the studio. Marble dust fills the air like snow. And there, revealed through the white haze, is the most magnificent statue {{BOTH_NAMES}} have ever seen‚Äîseventeen feet of perfect human form.\n\nA muscular man covered head to toe in white dust pauses his work. His eyes are fierce, focused. This is Michelangelo Buonarroti.\n\n'What do you want?' he growls. 'Can't you see I'm busy?'\n\nGiuliano bows nervously. 'Maestro, these young ones seek to learn‚Äî'\n\n'Then they can learn by watching.' Michelangelo returns to his work, but his voice softens slightly. 'This is David. The Biblical hero who defeated a giant with nothing but a sling and a stone. I've been working on him for three years.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} stares at the statue's face‚Äîdetermined, brave, afraid and courageous at once. 'How do you make stone look so... alive?'\n\nMichelangelo pauses. 'I don't create. I reveal. David was already in this marble. I just removed everything that wasn't him.'",
