        "botticelli-studio": {
            "id": "botticelli-studio",
            "summary": "They enter Botticelli's dream-like world of mythological paintings",
            "text": "Botticelli's studio feels like stepping into a dream. Soft light filters through gauze curtains. Paintings of gods and goddesses line the walls‚Äîgraceful figures dancing through forests of flowers.\n\nThe artist himself is gentler than {{BOTH_NAMES}} expected‚Äîa quiet man with thoughtful eyes. He's working on a painting of a woman rising from the sea on a seashell.\n\n'The Birth of Venus,' he explains softly. 'Venus, goddess of love and beauty, born from the foam of the sea. It's a story from ancient mythology, but really, it's about something more‚Äîthe way beauty enters the world, pure and perfect.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} leans closer. 'Her hair looks so real... like it's actually blowing in the wind.'\n\n'That took years to learn,' Botticelli smiles. 'Flowing fabric, moving hair, graceful poses‚Äîthese are the hardest things to capture. They require you to see motion, not just stillness. And color...' He holds up a shell filled with brilliant pink pigment. 'Color tells the emotional truth of a painting. What does this pink make you feel?'\n\n'Happy?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} offers. 'Gentle?'\n\n'Exactly! Color speaks directly to the heart.'",
