        "leonardo-inventions": {
            "id": "leonardo-inventions",
            "summary": "They see Leonardo's sketches for helicopters, tanks, and robots",
            "text": "Leonardo's notebooks are mind-bending. {{BOTH_NAMES}} see sketches of machines that shouldn't exist in 1504‚Äîhelicopters, tanks, submarines, robots!\n\n'These are... impossible,' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} breathes.\n\n'Nothing is impossible,' Leonardo says. 'Only things we haven't learned to build yet. I study birds to understand flight.' He shows sketches of wings, air currents, feathers examined in minute detail. 'Someday, humans will fly. I know it.'\n\nHe flips to another page‚Äîa mechanical knight, designed to sit up, wave its arms, and open its visor. 'This one I actually built! Gears and pulleys inside, like a clock, but shaped like a man.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} points to the mirror writing. 'Why do you write backward?'\n\n'Habit,' Leonardo chuckles. 'I'm left-handed‚Äîwriting this way is easier and doesn't smudge the ink. Also, it keeps my ideas private. But between you and me...' he winks, 'I just like puzzles.'\n\nHe grows serious. 'Art and science are not enemies. They are two ways of seeing the same world. Every artist should think like a scientist. Every scientist should see like an artist.'",
