        "michelangelo-philosophy": {
            "id": "michelangelo-philosophy",
            "summary": "Michelangelo explains his vision of freeing art from raw stone",
            "text": "Michelangelo sets down his chisel and faces them fully. 'Every block of stone has a statue inside it. The sculptor's task is to discover it and set it free.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} frowns. 'But... you decide what to carve, right?'\n\n'Do I?' He gestures at the massive David. 'This marble block was rejected by two other sculptors. They couldn't see what was inside. But when I looked at it, I saw David‚ÄîI felt David‚Äîstraining to emerge. My job was simply to remove the stone that imprisoned him.'\n\nHe picks up a small chip of marble. 'When I carve, I'm not adding anything. I'm taking away. Each chip brings me closer to the truth already hidden in the stone. That's why mistakes are so costly‚Äîonce you remove marble, you cannot put it back.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} looks at the statue with new eyes. 'So you have to see the whole thing before you even start?'\n\n'In my mind, completely. Then begins the slow, careful work of making what I see visible to everyone else. That is art: making the invisible visible.'",
