        "sculpting-lesson": {
            "id": "sculpting-lesson",
            "summary": "Michelangelo teaches them to feel the form within clay",
            "text": "Michelangelo hands each of them a small block of soft clay. 'Marble is too precious for beginners. But clay will teach you the basics. Close your eyes and feel the shape you want to create.'\n\n{{BOTH_NAMES}} close their eyes, clay cool in their hands.\n\n'Sculpture is touch as much as sight,' Michelangelo continues. 'You must feel the curves, the planes, the tensions. A body is not just shapes‚Äîit has weight, balance, movement. David is not standing still; he is about to move. Can you feel that?'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} squeezes and shapes the clay, trying to find the form within. It's harder than it looks‚Äîthe clay doesn't want to do what {{PLAYER1_HE_SHE}} imagines.\n\n'Frustrating, yes?' Michelangelo almost smiles. 'Good. The resistance teaches you. Every mistake is a lesson. I've been carving since I was a boy, and I still make mistakes. The difference is, I've learned to see them coming.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} holds up a lumpy but recognizable bird shape. Michelangelo nods approvingly. 'There! You found something. That's the beginning.'",
