        "sistine-chapel": {
            "id": "sistine-chapel",
            "summary": "Michelangelo describes painting the chapel ceiling while lying on scaffolding",
            "text": "'The Pope wants me to paint the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel,' Michelangelo sighs. 'I told him I'm a sculptor, not a painter. He didn't care.'\n\n'The Sistine Chapel?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} exclaims. They've seen pictures‚Äîthe famous image of God reaching out to Adam.\n\n'You know of it?' Michelangelo looks surprised. 'It's not finished yet. I've been lying on scaffolding for years, painting above my head. The paint drips in my eyes. My neck aches constantly. But...'\n\nHis expression softens. 'When I look up at what I've created‚Äîthe story of creation itself spreading across that ceiling‚ÄîI feel something I cannot describe. It is the hardest thing I've ever done. And perhaps the greatest.'\n\nHe shows them sketches‚Äîmuscular figures, swirling compositions, dramatic gestures. 'A ceiling cannot be seen all at once. So I designed it to unfold as you walk beneath it. Each panel leads to the next. The whole tells a story.'\n\n'It sounds painful,' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} says.\n\n'All great art requires suffering,' Michelangelo says quietly. 'Not because suffering is good, but because nothing worthwhile comes easily.'",
