            "text": "Botticelli sets up two small canvases. 'The secret to grace is the line. Watch.' His brush creates a single flowing curve‚Äîlike a wave, like hair blowing, like a dancer's arm.\n\n'Don't stop and start. One continuous motion. Let the brush breathe.'\n\n{{BOTH_NAMES}} try. Their first attempts are shaky, hesitant. But Botticelli is patient.\n\n'Feel the movement in your whole arm, not just your fingers. Art comes from the body, not just the hand. When you dance, you don't think about each muscle‚Äîyou feel the flow. Painting is the same.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} relaxes, lets the brush move more freely. The line becomes smoother, more alive.\n\n'There! See how different it feels? Stiff lines show fear‚Äîfear of mistakes. Flowing lines show confidence, even if they're not perfect. Better to be bold and wrong than timid and right.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} tries painting hair, each strand flowing into the next. It's not beautiful yet‚Äîbut there's something there. A hint of movement. A whisper of grace.\n\n'Art takes time,' Botticelli smiles. 'But you've made a beginning.'",
