            "summary": "At the Medici palace, they see how patrons support artists",
            "text": "The Medici palace is overwhelming‚Äîmarble floors, painted ceilings, sculptures in every niche. Guards in elegant uniforms eye them suspiciously until Giuliano produces a letter of introduction.\n\n'The Medici family has supported the arts for generations,' he explains as they walk through magnificent halls. 'Without their gold, most of these masterpieces would never exist. Art requires patrons‚Äîpeople who believe beauty is worth paying for.'\n\nThey enter a grand room where several artists have gathered, sketching, debating, laughing. {{PLAYER1_NAME}} spots Leonardo in one corner, arguing with an older man. Michelangelo broods in another, sketching furiously.\n\n'Even geniuses need support,' Giuliano says. 'Talent alone is not enough. You need materials, time, space, and someone who believes in your vision. The Medici gave that to hundreds of artists. That's why Florence leads the world in art.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} watches the artists interacting. 'They're learning from each other too.'\n\n'Of course! No artist exists alone. We study each other's work, compete, collaborate. The community makes everyone better.'",
